    "biography": "<p>Meks, towering metallic constructs 15 to 25 feet tall, roam any terrain as relics of a vanished race of insectoid sorcerers. Crafted with insect-like features—barrel chests, barbed, double-jointed limbs—some mimic giants or lizards, serving as guards for masters or wandering chaotically to assail all in their path.</p><p>Striking twice with heavy limbs for [[/r 1d6*10 #Limb damage]] each, they unleash a 20' paralyzing breath cloud, forcing a save vs. breath weapon each round or paralysis for [[/r 1d3 #Turns paralyzed]] turns. Cold slows them to half speed, but only disintegrate pierces their immunity to other spells.</p><p>Unintelligent yet responsive to simple commands when mastered, they appear singly ([[/r 1 #Meks encountered]]), their alignment shifting from lawful servitude to chaotic rampage without guidance. Their treasures vary, hoarded from fallen foes (HD 11, XP 2700).</p><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Any</p>",
